All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Account
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage an account.
    AccountType
    This enumeration defines the two types an Account can be: an ASSET or a LIABILITY.
    App  
    BasicAccount
    This class implements the interface Account and has the responsibility of managing a basic account.
    BasicMovement
    This class implements the interface Movement and has the responsibility of managing a single basic movement.
    BasicTag
    This class implements the interface Tag and has the responsibility of defining a tag/category.
    BasicTransaction
    This class implements the interface Transaction and has the responsibility of managing a basic transaction.
    Controller
    This interface is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to act as a bridge between the view and the model of the application.
    ExportManager
    This interface is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to export all data of a ledger into specific files of a certain extension.
    HasID
    This interface is implemented by all classes whose objects have a unique ID field that identifies them.
    ImportManager
    This interface is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to import all data from specific files of a certain extension into a ledger.
    Indexer
    This class has the responsibility to manage all IDs of all the accounts, tags, transactions and movements of the application.
    JavaFXAccountCreatorController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user create an Account..
    JavaFXAccountModifierController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user modify an already existing Account.
    JavaFXAccountRemoverController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user remove an already existing Account.
    JavaFXController
    This interface is implemented by all the classes of the GUI view of the app that have the responsibility to launch an Alert window or another JavaFX controller window in general.
    JavaFXEditor
    This interface is implemented by all the classes of the GUI view of the app that have the responsibility to interact with the controller to finalize specific actions.
    JavaFXJBudget
    This class implements the interface Application which is the entry point for JavaFX applications and has the responsibility to start the main Application window and then waits for the application to finish.
    JavaFXJBudgetController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and has the responsibility to manage the main window of the application as well as to let visualize all data of the application in tables.
    JavaFXMovementCreatorController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user create a Movement.
    JavaFXMovementRemoverController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user remove a Movement.
    JavaFXTagCreatorController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user create a Tag.
    JavaFXTagModifierController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user modify an existing Tag.
    JavaFXTagRemoverController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user remove an already existing Tag.
    JavaFXTransactionCreatorController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user create a Transaction.
    JavaFXTransactionRemoverController
    This class implements the interfaces JavaFXController and JavaFXEditor and has the responsibility to manage the window that lets the user remove an already existing Transaction.
    Ledger
    This interface is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage all data of the application.
    LedgerMenu
    This class implements the interface Ledger and has the responsibility to manage all data of the application.
    LedgerMenuController
    This class implements the interface Controller and has the responsibility to act as a bridge between the view and the model of the application.
    Movement
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage a single movement.
    MovementException
    This class extends the class Exception and has the responsibility to provide description for all possible errors deriving from the creation/removal of a movement.
    MovementType
    This enumeration defines the two types a Movement can be: an INCREMENT or a DECREMENT.
    Tag
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to define a tag/category.
    TextFileExporter
    This class implements the interface ExportManager and has the responsibility to export all data of the ledger in .txt files in a given path.
    TextFileImporter
    This class implements the interface ImportManager and has the responsibility to import all data from .txt files in a given path into a ledger.
    Transaction
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage a transaction.
